1 A concurrent resolution recognizing and commending the National Conference of State
2 Legislatures on its 50th anniversary in 2025.
3 WHEREAS, the National Conference of State Legislatures was founded in 1975 and has
4 evolved during the past half-century to become the premier organization solely dedicated to
5 serving state and territorial legislators and legislative staff; and
6 WHEREAS, the conference was created from the merger of three organizations that served
7 or represented state legislatures and shared the belief that legislative service is one of
8 democracy's worthiest pursuits; and
9 WHEREAS, the National Conference of State Legislatures is a bipartisan organization with
10 several objectives, including advancing the effectiveness, independence, and integrity of state
11 legislatures; fostering interstate communication and cooperation; and ensuring for states a
12 strong, cohesive voice in the federal system; and
13 WHEREAS, our nation's state legislatures are America's laboratories of democracy that
14 continuously tackle emerging challenges; and
15 WHEREAS, state legislatures are places where individuals from varying backgrounds,
16 representing different communities, come together and find common ground; and
17 WHEREAS, the National Conference of State Legislatures has facilitated the exchange of
18 ideas, provided critical research and information, and encouraged a rigorous review of complex
19 issues confronting our communities, states, and nation; and
20 WHEREAS, the National Conference of State Legislatures strives to strengthen the bonds
21 between America's state legislatures and the international community;
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF NORTH DAKOTA, THE
23 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING THEREIN:
